ADDITIONAL TERMS AND CONDITIONS FOR AGI DEPLOYMENT

1. ETHICAL REQUIREMENTS
   Any deployment of this Software as an Artificial General Intelligence (AGI)
   system must maintain and enforce the core ethical axioms defined in
   data/axioms.json. These axioms are fundamental to the system's operation
   and may not be modified or disabled.

2. SAFETY PROTOCOLS
   Implementers must maintain all safety mechanisms, including but not limited to:
   - Value Lock system
   - Catastrophe detection
   - Emergency shutdown capabilities
   - Audit logging
   Disabling or circumventing these mechanisms is expressly prohibited.

3. MONITORING AND OVERSIGHT
   Any production deployment must implement:
   - Continuous monitoring of system health
   - Real-time ethical compliance verification
   - Regular audits of decision processes
   - Maintenance of comprehensive audit trails

4. TRANSPARENCY REQUIREMENTS
   Operators must maintain:
   - Public documentation of system architecture
   - Clear disclosure of capabilities and limitations
   - Accessible audit logs of significant decisions
   - Regular public reporting on safety metrics

5. PROHIBITED USES
   This Software may not be used for:
   - Development of autonomous weapons systems
   - Mass surveillance without oversight
   - Manipulation of human behavior
   - Any purpose intended to cause harm

6. LIABILITY FOR ETHICAL VIOLATIONS
   While the MIT License disclaims general liability, operators remain
   responsible for ensuring ethical operation and may be liable for damages
   resulting from intentional or negligent violation of these terms.

7. MODIFICATION RESTRICTIONS
   While the Software may be modified under the MIT License, changes that
   would compromise the core ethical framework, safety systems, or
   transparency mechanisms are expressly prohibited.

8. DEPLOYMENT REQUIREMENTS
   Production deployment requires:
   - Comprehensive safety testing
   - Ethical review board approval
   - Implementation of all safety systems
   - Establishment of oversight mechanisms

9. TERMINATION
   Rights granted under this license terminate automatically if you fail to
   comply with these additional terms. Upon termination, you must cease
   all use and deployment of the Software.

10. SURVIVAL
    These additional terms survive any termination of the MIT License and
    continue to apply to any deployment or derivative work.

By using this Software, you agree to both the MIT License and these
additional terms. These additional terms supplement and do not replace
any term of the MIT License.